$","span",null,{"children":"6 min read"}]]}]]}],["$","article",null,{"className":"ArticleLayout_content___Im_T","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":"The aftermath of the COVID-19 pandemic multiplied by the uncertainty and rapid change spawned by AI has created a dynamic in which Modern organizations operate within increasingly complex systems—where markets, technology, regulation, and human behavior interact in non-linear ways. As a result of these novel factors, in which the proverbial book has not yet been written, traditional strategic models often fail, not simply because of poor execution, but because they oversimplify the new reality in which we all suddenly find ourselves. At Metaratus®, we recognize that while complexity cannot be eliminated, it must be understood through what we call a “prismatic approach”, meaning one that disaggregates the myriad entangled variables that feed into the composite outcome from one another, so that they can be individually understood and tested in isolation, a necessary step to understanding the role that each puzzle piece plays in the aggregate outcome."}],"$L6","$L7","$L8","$L9","$La","$Lb","$Lc","$Ld","$Le","$Lf","$L10"]}]]}],"$L11"],["$L12","$L13"],"$L14"]}],{},null,false]},null,false]},null,false]},null,false],"$L15",false]],"m":"$undefined","G":["$16",[]],"s":false,"S":true}
